[1]
Date: 20 Dec 2005
From: Gary Greenberg <gngreenberg@gmail.com>
Source: Itar-Tass news agency [edited]
<http://www.itar-tass.com/eng/level2.html?NewsID=2737795&PageNum=0>

13 schoolchildren were hospitalized in Chechnya's Shelkovskoi district
Tuesday, with symptoms of an unknown disease, the emergency situations
center of the southern region told Itar-Tass.
"4 children in the village of Staroglazovskaya are in grave condition. They
have fever, headache and numbness in the limbs, but there's no vomiting,
diarrhea or high temperature," the duty officer said.
The 1st reports about an outbreak of the disease came on 16 Dec 2005. At
that time, 12 pupils of the local school together with 2 teachers were
rushed to the village hospital.
Specialists ruled out food poisoning. Head of the Shelkovskoi district
administration Khusein Nukhayev suggested that the cause is a poison gas,
but its type has defied analysis so far.
A mobile laboratory is to arrive at the village from Rostov-on-Don on
Tuesday. The school has been closed for toxicity expert examination. A
group of doctors from Chechnya's disaster medicine center is working at the
scene.
Chechen prosecutors instituted criminal proceedings over breach of sanitary
and epidemiological norms.
--
Gary Greenberg
<gngreenberg@gmail.com
